Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.16,0:00:04.88,English,,0,0,0,,A country of 20 million people recorded 1 \Nmillion deaths during a deadly pandemic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.16,0:00:04.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在一次致命瘟疫中 一个国家中的两千万人中有一百万人死亡
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.68,0:00:09.20,English,,0,0,0,,More than half of these deaths had \Nbeen vaccinated against the disease,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.68,0:00:09.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在死亡人数中有一半接种了针对这种疾病的疫苗
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.20,0:00:12.56,English,,0,0,0,,but this rate was only marginally \Ndifferent to the remaining population.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.20,0:00:12.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但在幸存的人当中这个（疫苗接种的）比例只有很小的出入
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.12,0:00:18.16,English,,0,0,0,,This led many to conclude that vaccination had \Nhad no effect on the mortality rate. In fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.12,0:00:18.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这将会导出疫苗针对降低死亡率无效的结论
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.16,0:00:23.20,English,,0,0,0,,it appeared that being vaccinated even increased \Nthe chance of death. However a statistician put
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.16,0:00:23.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上 看起来似乎接种反而增加了死亡风险
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.20,0:00:28.16,English,,0,0,0,,these deaths into three different age groups, \Nand found the opposite trend. Within each group,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.20,0:00:28.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然而一位统计学家将这些死亡数分在三个不同的年龄组中 由此发现了相反的趋势
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.16,0:00:33.36,English,,0,0,0,,those vaccinated were far less likely to die from \Nthe disease. This apparent contradiction is known
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.16,0:00:33.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在每一组中 接种者的死亡风险都远远更低
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.36,0:00:38.24,English,,0,0,0,,as "Simpson's Paradox", where the aggregate of all \Nthe data shows a trend that is opposite to that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.36,0:00:38.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个明显的矛盾被称为辛普森悖论 它强调所有数据展现的趋势可能和分组数据截然相反
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.24,0:00:43.20,English,,0,0,0,,when broken down into groups. It's usually the \Nresult of other factors not shown on the graph.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.24,0:00:43.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它通常是由没有在图表中展示的因素导致的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.76,0:00:48.48,English,,0,0,0,,In this example, it is that being old \Nindependently increases the likelihood of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.76,0:00:48.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这个例子中 年长因素独立地对死亡风险和受接种概率有贡献
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.48,0:00:53.76,English,,0,0,0,,and the likelihood of being vaccinated. So \Nin this case, using only the combined data
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.48,0:00:53.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以此情况下 仅仅使用总体的数据
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.76,0:00:57.84,English,,0,0,0,,to draw conclusion about the vaccine's \Neffectiveness would be incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.76,0:00:57.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,得到有关疫苗有效性的结论是不正确的
